data.text:
Šimon Ornest is a Czech singer, musician, educator, bandleader, and manager of the group The Tap Tap. Born on December 18, 1974, in Prague, he has made significant contributions to the Czech music scene through his roles in performance and education. His involvement as a manager and bandleader showcases his multifaceted talent and dedication to music, enriching the cultural landscape in the Czech Republic.
